You can also visit the spot where the island was first bought nearby. We call it Upstate Manhattan!
notes: This is a great location for parents or friends coming to visit students at Columbia or Fordham. Fordham is a 20 minute bus ride away on the Bx12, and Columbia is 20 minutes on the 1. My family loves being able to stay with me in Manhattan, and we all love the easy commute to school events. For the convenience and price it's a win-win. Blessed with our little girl Samantha, we strive to be better people everyday with the little things in life.  We used to run thru the nightclubs and live the crazy lifestyle...we couldn't live without late night movies, the latest bar/lounge/club, being in "THE IT" crowd, running off to Paris or a quick trip to Vegas at a moments notice for a few days!

We  enjoy going to ethnic restaurants and exploring tastes while exposing our girl to all NYC has to offer.  

As we are a mixed couple, living within this diverse city gives us a sense of home that we cherish.  We are a small family with a HUGE extended family that live in the New York and Maryland area and work hard developing our relationships with our family.  

When we travel we appreciate a host that welcomes us like family, but stays out of our business.  Thats what you can expect from us.  We want to be available to you if you need, but otherwise, enjoy your privacy and have fun.  We believe that being a good person is crucial and that good things happen to good people.  That is what we are....good people.
